<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="201" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[173,660,1282,1729]" lastBlockId="11.[707,1193,194,400]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,294,1522,1543]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1899" box="[313,494,1522,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Psalidoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holubi">
<emphasis box="[313,494,1522,1543]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">Psalidoma holubi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a series of specimens from the collection of O. Nickerl (currently part of the NMP collection), and part of the series was retained by Spaeth. They were collected by E. Holub during his second expedition to 
<collectingCountry box="[282,407,1655,1676]" name="South Africa" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Spaeth, F." box="[450,585,1655,1676]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201" pagination="213 - 221" refId="ref15457" refString="Spaeth, F. 1899. Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassididen nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen. III. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch- Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 49 (4): 213 - 221 + pl. 5." type="journal article" year="1899">Spaeth (1899)</bibRefCitation>
did not select 
<specimenCount box="[234,365,1681,1702]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
as the type, all specimens are 
<typeStatus box="[173,259,1708,1729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">syntypes</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Borowiec, L." box="[269,431,1708,1729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201" refId="ref14733" refString="Borowiec, L. 2002. A Monograph of the Afrotropical Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Part 3. Revision of the Tribe Cassidini 1, Except the Genera Aethiopocassis Sp., Cassida L., and Chiridopsis Sp. Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 292 pp. + 17 pls." type="book" year="2002">Borowiec (2002)</bibRefCitation>
intended to designate a 
<typeStatus box="[707,794,194,215]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this species, as he listed the 
<typeStatus box="[1086,1169,194,215]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">syntypes</typeStatus>
as “ 
<typeStatus box="[717,804,220,241]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount box="[855,1011,220,241]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">6 paralectotypes</specimenCount>
”, but did not provide an adequate statement of designation. Therefore, the requirements of Article 74.7.3 (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" pageId="11" pageNumber="201" refId="ref15262" refString="ICZN. 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
) were not met, and the specimens remain 
<typeStatus box="[707,793,326,347]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">syntypes</typeStatus>
. However, we have examined the series and it is consistent; thus, there is no formal need for a 
<typeStatus box="[760,847,379,400]" pageId="11" pageNumber="201">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
